This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image captioning and image generation. It also involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which are commonly used in the sub-category. 

The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text generation and captioning, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. 

Additionally, the paper proposes improvements to existing text conditioned image generation techniques, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the integration of multiple modalities (visual and text), which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
